{
  "name": "Wind Release Rakshasa Barrier",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Wind.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You raise your hand and generate an intensely dense torrent of wind that circles around you, creating a bubble of wind that envelops your entire body.</p><p>The bubble of wind that envelops you has a number of hit points equal to your Proficiency bonus times your Ninjutsu ability Modifier. This bubble has Resistance to Wind and Lightning Damage and vulnerability to Fire Damage. If this jutsu would trigger an additional effect as listed below, as a result of a different damage type, creatures in the effects range must make a Dexterity saving throw to avoid its effects.</p><p>If the bubble would take Lightning damage, all creatures within 15 feet of you must succeed a Dexterity saving throw becoming shocked on a failed save, as lightning jumps from you to other creatures around you.</p><p>If the bubble would take Cold damage, all creatures within 15 feet of you must succeed a Dexterity saving throw becoming chilled on a failed save, as the cold is spread to all creatures around you.</p><p>If the bubble would take Earth damage, all creatures within 15 feet of you must succeed a Dexterity saving throw, gaining the bleeding condition on a failed save, as they are pelted with shrapnel of earth.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above C-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3, the size of the area affected by 5 feet, and the number of hit points your bubble has by +10.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
    "source": {
      "custom": ""
    },
